Please read ALL

Reservations are HIGHLY recommended for  ALL Tea Parties.

     If requesting the Children's Fairyland Tea room, you MUST call and NOT use the web form.

Saturdays are most often very busy, and it is possible that we may not be able to accept

your reservation request for one of those days. We suggest that you plan well ahead

for a Saturday event. (The same goes for other days, such as Holidays)

For groups of 12 or more:  Please call us - do not use the Web-Form on this site.

A non-refundable deposit of $150.00 is required - which will be applied to your final bill. If the number of guests is less than the original reservation number, please contact us no later than 48 hours before your party, or you will be charged for that original number.


If you call, and do not receive an answer (common during business hours), please leave a message with your name, number, reservation request, and we will call you back.

If you contact us using our contact form (email), a reply to your message/request is

absolutely necessary before the reservation is actually made.

When making a Reservation Request, we need ALL the details of your reservation,

Date/Time/Number in your party/Which Tea Party or ordering from the menu/Special requirements (disabled persons, private area).

CHILDREN - our restaurant caters to a refined clientele, and if you will be bringing children in, we request that you PLEASE keep them with you at all times and regulate their behavior in a manner that will offer all of our visitors the most pleasant experience.

UPDATE (June 12): WE ARE OPEN with updated procedures every day 10am to 5pm. (NOTE: Masks are required at all times, even outside, unless seated at a table or actively participating in a tasting) All indoor tastings should be reserved ahead of time online or by calling the winery. Click this banner for full details about changes to our tasting procedures.

 Wine Tasting GlassesTaste & Tour


Your experience at Wagner Vineyards for a wine tasting should be fun, educational, delicious, and safe. We have some new health and safety requirements for employees and visitors at the winery to help keep you and our staff and families safe. All indoor tastings now require a reservation, regardless of the number of tasters, to help us maintain social distancing within the building as well as to allow for cleaning between scheduled tastings. Visit our Online Reservation page to schedule your visit now. We are not currently taking reservations for flights at the outdoor picnic tables – picnic tables are first-come-first-served and the flights can be purchased at the outdoor bar (note: masks are required when ordering at the outdoor bar).

For everyone’s health and safety

On the day of your tasting, if you are feeling unwell, please stay home. We are asking the same of our staff and each day, when arriving at work, all staff members will take their temperature and will not be permitted to work if they are showing any symptoms of a virus. When you arrive at the winery for your tasting, be sure to bring a mask. Masks are required at all times on the premises unless you are sitting at a table or actively participating in a tasting. Please note, that masks must also be worn outside when not seated at a table. You will find touchless hand sanitizing stations throughout the facility and we encourage everyone, guests and staff alike, to sanitize often, and especially before a tasting. In addition to the safeguards mentioned above, we will have in place various additional precautions during your tastings as well as throughout the facility for the duration of your visit.

What to expect during your wine tasting

Wagner Vineyards offers more than 30 wines, so you are sure to find something to suit your palate here. We focus on “Customer Choice” tastings where we work with you to select the wines you’ll most enjoy. Wine tastings are $8 and include a sampling of 5 wines, a complimentary glass to take home, and a coupon for $4 off a purchase of $25 or more. During your tasting, you will notice a plexiglass barrier separating our staff from you for everyone’s safety as this is one of the few times you are permitted to remove your mask. In addition to the plexiglass, our staff members will wear masks at all times while pouring and serving.

Visiting the winery after your tasting (or without a tasting)

Visitors are welcome to use the picnic tables outside, weather permitting, to enjoy wine by the glass, flight, or bottle or beer by the pint or flight. The picnic tables have been placed at a minimum of 6 feet apart and there is a maximum of 8 people allowed per table. The tables should not be moved. At this time, we are not taking reservations for the outdoor picnic tables and they can be used on a first-come-first-served basis.

Should you have any questions or concerns about visiting the winery for a tasting, please feel free to contact us through the form on our contact page or call us at 607-582-6450.

Guided Winery Tours

At this time, we are unable to offer guided winery tours on a daily basis. Check back for updates as regulations continue to change as part of UnPause NY.

School Meals

school meal guides links and recommendations

Tasty and nutritious meals are prepared in our school kitchen offering pupils and staff a variety of meat, fish and vegetarian dishes. Children also have the option to bring their own packed lunch.

School meals

If you would like your child to have school meals (whether paid for or Free School Meal) we require that you let us know at the start of day

Meals are charged at £2.10 a day (£10.50 a week) and must be paid for at least the night before  your child requires lunch.  You can pay using the online School Parentmail system. 

Funding is allocated to children who are currently on Free School Meals (FSM) or have been on FSM at any time over the last six years (the Ever6 measure), to those with families in the regular armed forces, to children currently in Local Authority Care or children who have been in care in the past.

School Menu

You can download a copy of the current menu here.

Eligible for Free School Meals?

If you think your child may be eligible for Free School Meals please apply online on East Sussex County Council, the Local Authority who are responsible for assessing whether your child is eligible for Free School Meals.

Packed lunches

We teach and promote healthy eating because on the basis that a well-balanced diet can have a positive impact on children’s health, behaviour and achievement. If your child is having packed lunches please follow these reminders:

 The main element should be savoury such as a sandwich, filled pitta bread, wrap, pasta or rice salad.

 Aim to include at least one portion of vegetables or salad.

 Include at least one portion of fruit. This could be a fruit salad, a piece of fresh fruit or dried fruit.

 For an extra snack, a fruit yogurt, fromage frais or rice cakes could be included.

 Although we do not recommend sweet desserts, we accept that you may wish to pack your child a small piece of cake or a biscuit.

 Water is provided by the school, however, you may provide a plastic bottle of water in your child’s lunchbox if you prefer.

 Please do not provide your child with chocolate, sweets, or a fizzy drink.

Packing a healthy lunch

Nuts and other allergies

Please make sure that any snacks and packed lunches brought to the school are nut free. Please do not use chocolate spread or peanut butter.

Wahaca Gift Vouchers
Our gift vouchers are available in denominations of £10 and £25. The vouchers will be valid in any of our restaurants for the next year from the date of purchase. They’ll arrive in a gift card wallet and there’s a ‘Sent By’ field you can fill out before checkout if they’re going straight to the lucky recipient. Unfortunately we cannot give change from gift voucher payments when they are redeemed.

Your vouchers will be sent to you by Royal Mail post.
Recorded delivery costs £2.69 with a 1 – 3 working day delivery window. Special delivery costs £7.49 guaranteeing next working day delivery by 1pm (if ordered before 1pm the day prior).
All orders received before 1pm  will be dispatched the same working day where possible, while orders received after 1pm will be dispatched the next working day. We’re afraid the vouchers cannot be emailed or purchased direct from any of our branches.

Receiving your vouchers
Both methods above mean someone will need to be there to sign for the delivery, so if you (or the recipient) are not home during the day, you might like to get them sent to a work address or trustworthy neighbour. If the delivery is missed, they’ll get sent to your local post office for collection.

Anything Else
If you have any questions, please drop us a line on ola@wahaca.co.uk.

Boarding students are entitled to up to 19 meals per week in the Evans Center Dining Hall. Breakfast, lunch and dinner is served Monday through Friday, brunch and dinner on Sunday coinciding with the posted Dining Hall hours of operation. You may only enter the Dining Hall once during each meal period.

Guests can purchase meals with cash or credit: $5.50 breakfast, $7.50 lunch, $9.50 dinner, $9.50 brunch (tax not included). Children under 10 $2.95 for all meals offered.

Your student ID card will give you access to the Dining Hall through the One Card System, and will be activated upon the first day of classes. The system will track your meals used throughout the week and reset back to your meal plan meals on Monday mornings. The system will also track your Dining Dollars.


You will not be allowed access into the Dining Hall without your valid ID card.

ID cards are not transferable.

Unused meals are not refundable. Guest may purchase using block meal plans, Dining Dollars, cash and credit.

The Evans Commons Dining Hall is "all you care to eat." There are no to-go plates/drinks. Containers brought from home may not be used to take food out of the Dining Hall. All food must be consumed in the dining room.


We always make every effort to follow the menus as posted. However, business demands may necessitate replacing certain items without prior notice. We apologize for any inconvenience this may cause.

New Yorker Bagels

Bagel Handling Instructions

You gotta treat us like one of your own…

This is a fresh, all-natural product made with love in New York City. Since there are no preservatives of any kind, leaving these out for more than 1 day will make ‘em stale.

Enjoy a fresh bagel or two now, and freeze the rest. These fresh bagels freeze wonderfully, and will last a full year when frozen. 

Yo – I’m dyin’ in here!

For both protection and as a convenient way to freeze, we place our bagels in plastic sleeves after cooling. BUT… the lack of air in the plastic sleeve can affect quality in transit, especially in warm weather. 

Take your bagels out of the plastic bag and – like a fine Chianti – let ‘em breathe for 15 minutes prior to eating or toasting. This exposure to air helps restore the proper consistency throughout. 

Turn up ‘da heat

When you’re ready to enjoy another fresh bagel after freezing: 

  1. Take out of the freezer and thaw on-counter – for about 30 minutes
  2. Preheat your over to 400°
  3. Place bagels on a baking pan and bake for 4 minutes

This method will provide the crispy outside and soft chewy inside of an authentic New York City bagel. (Any bagels not enjoyed after heating up this way, must be discarded - ain’t there always a catch?)

No Nukes

Nothing destroys the proper texture and consistency of a real bagel like microwaving – please don’t use the microwave. Don’t make me tell ya twice…
